    </p>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Bewys die bostaande formule!
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <p>
      Ons kan nou die volgende stelling bewys.
    </p>

    <theorem>
      <title>Basisomskakeling</title>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Veronderstel dat <m>\basis{B} = \bopen
          \ve{b}_1, \ldots, \ve{b}_n\bclose</m> en
          <m>\basis{C} = \bopen \ve{c}_1,
          \ldots, \ve{c}_n \bclose</m> basisse vir 'n vektorruimte <m>V</m> is, en laat
          <m>\mat{P}_{\basis{C} \leftarrow \basis{B}}</m> die
          basiskomskakelingsmatriks van
          <m>\basis{B}</m> na <m>\basis{C}</m> wees.
          Dan, vir
          alle vektore <m>\ve{v}</m> in <m>V</m>,
          <men xml:id="change-of-basis-in-action">
            [\ve{v}]_\basis{C} = \mat{P}_{\basis{C} \leftarrow \basis{B}}
            [\ve{v}]_\basis{B} 
          </men>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </theorem>

    <proof>
      <p>
        Laat <m>\ve{v} \in V</m>.
        Brei <m>\ve{v}</m> uit in die basis <m>\basis{B}</m>:
        <me>
          \ve{v} = a_1 \ve{b}_1 + a_2 \ve{b}_2 + \cdots + a_n \ve{b}_n, 
          \mbox{i.e. }  [\ve{v}]_\basis{B} = \cvector{a_1 \\ \vdots \\ a_n}
        </me>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Dan,
        <md>
          <mrow>_\basis{C} \amp = [a_1 \ve{b}_1 + \cdots + a_n
          \ve{b}_n]_\basis{C}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp = a_1 [\ve{b}_1]_\basis{C} + \cdots + a_n [\ve{b}_n]_\basis{C}  \amp \amp 
          \mbox{(volgens <xref ref="lin_of_coord_vectors">Lemma</xref>)}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp = \left[ \cvector{</mrow>
          <mrow>\ve{b}_1</mrow>
          <mrow>}_\basis{C} \, \cvector{</mrow>
          <mrow>\ve{b}_2</mrow>
          <mrow>}_\basis{C} \, \cdots \, \cvector{</mrow>
          <mrow>\ve{b}_n</mrow>
          <mrow>}_\basis{C}\right] \cvector{a_1</mrow>
          <mrow>\vdots</mrow>
          <mrow>a_n} \amp \amp 
          \mbox{(volgens (3.5.6))}</mrow>
          <mrow>\amp =    \mat{P}_{\basis{C} \leftarrow \basis{B}} [\ve{v}]_\basis{B}
          \, </mrow>
        </md>.
      </p>
    </proof>

    <example>
      <statement>
        <p>
          In ons deurlopende voorbeeld,
          s&#xea; die stelling dat vir
          <em>enige</em> vektor <m>\ve{v} \in \mathbb{R}^2</m>,
          <md>
            [\ve{v}]_\basis{C} = \cmatrix{1 \amp  2 \\ 3 \amp  3} [\ve{v}]_\basis{B} .
          </md>
        </p>

        <p>
          Dit geld dan ook vir ons vektor <m>\ve{w}</m>,
          waarvan die ko&#xf6;rdinate in
          die basis <m>\ve{B}</m> is:
          <me>
            [\ve{w}]_\basis{B} = \cvector{ -3 \\ 2} 
          </me>.
        </p>

        <p>
          So in hierdie geval s&#xea; die stelling dat
          <md>
            [\ve{w}]_{\basis{C}} = \cmatrix{1 \amp  2 \\ 3 \amp  3} \cvector{-3 \\ 2}
            = \cvector{1 \\ -3}
          </md>
          wat met ons vorige berekening <xref ref="w_in_basis_C" /> ooreenstem!
        </p>
      </statement>
    </example>

    <p>
      \furtherexercises
    </p>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Dit is 'n voortsetting van <xref ref="matrix_basis_exercise">Oefening</xref>.
          Beskou die volgende twee basisse vir
          <m>\Mat_{2,2}</m>:
          <md>
            \basis{B}  = {  \bopen} \mat{B}_1 = \cmatrix{1 \amp  0 \\ 0 \amp  1},
            \, \mat{B}_2 = \cmatrix{1 \amp  0 \\ 0 \amp  -1}, \, \mat{B}_3 = \cmatrix{1
            \amp  1 \\ 1 \amp  1}, \, \mat{B}_4 = \cmatrix{0 \amp  1 \\ -1 \amp  0} {
            \bclose}
          </md>
          <md>
            \basis{C} = { \bopen} \mat{C}_1 = \cmatrix{1 \amp  1 \\ 0 \amp  0}, \,
            \mat{C}_2 = \cmatrix{1 \amp  -1 \\ 0 \amp  0}, \, \mat{C}_3 = \cmatrix{0 \amp 
            0 \\ 1 \amp  1}, \, \mat{C}_4 = \cmatrix{0 \amp  0 \\ 1 \amp  -1} {
            \bclose}
          </md>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <title>(a)</title>
              <p>
                Bereken die basisomskakelingmatrikse
                <m>\mat{P}_{\basis{C}
                \leftarrow \basis{B}}</m> en <m>\mat{P}_{\basis{B} \leftarrow
                \basis{C}}</m>.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <title>(b)</title>
              <p>
                Bereken <m>[\mat{A}]_\basis{B}</m> en <m>[\mat{A}]_\basis{C}</m>,
                waar
                <md>
                  A = \cmatrix{1 \amp  2 \\ 3 \amp  4}
                </md>
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <title>(c)</title>
              <p>
                Gaan na dat <m>[\mat{A}]_\basis{C} = \mat{P}_{\basis{C}
                \leftarrow \basis{B}} [\mat{A}]_\basis{B}</m> en dat
                <m>[\mat{A}]_\basis{B} = \mat{P}_{\basis{B} \leftarrow \basis{C}}
                [\mat{A}]_\basis{C}</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Bereken die basisomskakelingmatriks
          <m>\mat{P}_{\basis{B} \leftarrow
          \basis{S}}</m> van die standaardbasis
          <me>
            \basis{S} = \bopen 1, \cos x, \sin x, \cos 2x, \sin 2x \bclose
          </me>
          van <m>\Trig_2</m> na die basis
          <me>
            \basis{B} = \bopen 1, \cos x, \sin x, \cos^2 x, \sin^2 x \bclose \,

          </me>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>
</section>

